   <div class="panel" id="rules">
  <details>
    <summary>Survival Protocols</summary>
    <div class="panel-content">
<p>1. While discussion is allowed, moderation rulings are final and not open to debate. This group is not run by popular vote or outside influence.</p>
<p>2. Inclusivity is a requirement; pushing players out or ignoring them for friends or shipping is not allowed.</p>
<p>3. Minimum activity is a requirement: You have two weeks to post in an interactive scene (not selfie posts or throwing out shitposts), after which the character will be considered inactive and removed. Staff has capability to check for posts via post history. This rule goes <b>per character,</b> not per player.</p>
<p>4. Every player is limited to five characters total. You cannot reserve faces for future characters or NPCs.</p>
<p>5. All characters at this time are strictly human with no superpowers or abilities.</p>
<p>6. All FCs must be 18+ (pictures used must be them over the age of 18); no deceased FCs.</p>
<p>7. Resources are finite, so please keep that in mind to keep consistency in the setting; there is food scarcity, no infinite ammo or water, and limited access to medicine.</p>
<p>8. For more in-depth information regarding the world, please check the "In-World Mechanics" section.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
</div>

    
